node.text:
This match was a battle of the ankles, but straight ankle locks won’t tap me, my ankle and calf hurt like a bitch still, but we pulled thru for the win with points on this one. Had some good transitions, w horrible arm bar attempt lol. He almost tapped to the same x choke as previous match but I let him up to play some more, bad bow and arrow attemp, back choke etc. trying for something diff. I feel I dominated every match, just need to learn the point system better. 3 wins 1 loss. Not too shabby. 
Not time to get knee surgery😫 no pain no gain.

node.text:
I knew my gi game was strong so I decided to be a warrior and limp out on to the Matt, the ref ask if I was ok and I said yes, bit it was hurting bad! The adrenaline got me thru it.
This match the guy was strong, but I took it slow, had a plan going in, and executed on it exactly. Tried for a quick take down but that didn’t work so I Pulled open guard, quick Scissor to mount and X choke for the tap. You can see me limping of at the end 😣

node.text:
This match I wasn’t thinking about points, since I just got of a quick submission win the fist match so I was going for the kill. I didn’t receive 4 points for a back take or a take down since I didn’t hold control for 2/3 seconds, I would of won it, but now I know. Almost had armbar at the end, he said he was about to tap but knew there were only a few seconds left
Lost buy points on this one, learned my lesson, and will get better!
This fight did re injure my knee, and could not walk on it afterwards nor could straight it all the way, I think torn meniscus. I was about to quit after this, cristi didn’t want me to continue, my coach almost called off the next match, but I had to push thru!

node.text:
Was feeling pretty good after this win!
Nerves were shot going in tho!
He took me down, pulled guard, went straight for the Kimora, rolled straight to mount. Went for head arm choke, almost got the tap. Let it go, quick back take while still holding the Kimora grip, transition to arm-bar for the tap.

node.text:
We work, we learn and then we celebrate 🍾

I’m so grateful for every single one of you who came down to Miami to learn and grow this past weekend!

I’m also grateful for everyone in our amazing mentorship community because without YOU this wouldn’t be possible.

We are all on a mission!

A mission to learn, to grow and to give back our knowledge.

Let’s take this to the next level!

If you are watching this and you are ready to join our team send me a DM and let’s get you started!

See you at the top 🚀 

Video credits: 🎥@sergiodoblel 🎥

#millionairementor #teamlfg
